beer_description: This is a beer made with real pumpkins. We hand-roasted over 500lbs of heirloom pumpkins from La Tercera Farms in Bodega Bay. The caramelized gourds were then added to our velvety American Barleywine and aged in brandy barrels for a year. Finally, we blended the barrel-aged beer with freshly brewed ale and added a delicate hint of pumpkin pie spices to round out this decadent autumn sipper.

Punkuccino :: Coffee Pumpkin Ale. 
A pumpkin ale with the attitude of a world-weary barista, Punkuccino packs a short shot of Stumptown coffee toddy in your pint with just a shake of cinnamon and nutmeg.  Pale, brown, biscuit, C-77 crystal, chocolate and kiln-coffee malts provide the body, German Northern Brewer lends a touch of bitterness, and lactose sweetens just a touch. Three pumpkin additions, in the mash, kettle and fermenter. 5% ABV.
Pumpkin Stout aged in Rum Barrels

Jolly Pumpkin Artisan Ales (Dexter, MI) and  Maui Brewing Co (Lahaina, Maui, HI) collaborated to create  Sobrehumano Palena ‘ole or “superhuman”. It is actually Maui’s first collaboration in a can, brewed with passionfruit and cherries.  This is Jolly Pumpkin’s edition of the collab.  Each brewery will add its own unique spin – as Maui will ferment normally (arriving in cans), and Jolly Pumpkin will make it  a barrel aged sour (in bottles). The beer was designed with two noble fruits from the two states Cherries & liliko’i.
Pumpkinator aged on Maker's Mark Bourbon barrels.

This fall favorite conjures up visions of crisp autumn nights, bright autumn colors, and fresh baked pumpkin pie. Boasting plenty of pumpkin spice, yet refreshingly drinkable, each sip finishes clean and crisp, beckoning the next. Mother, may I have another?
A seasonal favorite!  Now available in cans from all Four Peaks locations!
Imperial Pumpkin ale crafted with roasted butternut squash, maple syrup and pirate rum spices added.
Stout brewed with pumpkin and spices

This batch is fermented with an ale yeast as opposed to last year's lager batch.

Our Brandy Barrel-Aged Imperial Pumpkin Ale pays homage to Lakefront’s formative years and to our Wisconsin roots. It pours a copper-orange with a fine, off-white head. The aroma is caramel-forward, followed by cinnamon, vanilla, nutmeg, oak, and subtle brandy notes. The full, moderately bright mouthfeel starts  with cinnamon, nutmeg, and caramel malt, then yields Madagascar vanilla bean, oak, and brandy flavors. A lingering oak and malty sweetness are left on the palate; a reminder of how we’ve honed our craft over the years.


Like our Pumpkin Lager, this goes great with fall meals, but the intense flavors demand richer foods. Roasted or glazed foul will pair excellently: we suggest honey glazed turkey or roasted duck. Try sweet potato and butternut squash hash as a side, or a spiced butternut squash purée. Also a great a dessert beer: serve it with French vanilla ice cream topped with maple glazed walnuts or a simple bread pudding with dried cranberry and pecans.

Bourbon Barrel-aged Imperial Stout with rich aromas of espresso and dark chocolate, and smooth roasted malt flavor, aged for 6 months in charred oak bourbon barrels with pumpkin spice to add the natural vanilla and caramelized sugar flavors of the wood, and the cinnamon, nutmeg, and ginger essence of the spice to the beer.

Gourd of Thunder is a dark and gnarly Imperial Pumpkin Porter brewed with freshly picked local pumpkins that were ripened on the vine while continuously listening to heavy metal.  The malty pumpkin backbone fuses robustly with a milky sugar creaminess.  Bourbon vanilla beans lay down a rock-steady foundation that drives the cinnamon, ginger and clove spices through your skull.  This brew does not merely mimic the flavor of a mortal pumpkin pie.  Gourd of Thunder will cataclysmically blow your mind with its face-melting, high-voltage attitude.  Headbangers Unite!

Malt:  Pale, Whole Wheat, Munich
Hops:  Willamette and Saphir
Yeast:  Top-fermenting English
Color:  Honey
Aroma:  Oak spiced, vanilla, nutmeg and cinnamon
Body:  Light to medium
Finish:  Warming, smooth and velvety
SRM:  14.85

Adding organic baby bear pumpkins to malt and hops makes this truly a local farm to brewhouse collaboration. A custom blend of six spices rounds out the flavors in this highly anticipated beer. *2011 GABF Gold Medal winner - Field and Pumpkin Beer*

beer_name: Barrel Aged Frog's Hollow Double Pumpkin
beer_description: Aged in Whiskey Barrels

Reserve Series
Released: September 2014

Tired of the everyday pumpkin beer?  At Terrapin, we've set out to make one with more character...a lot more character.  Bring this great feast of a beer to your favorite fall gathering and share with everyone who attends.  Brewed with a cornucopia of deep, rich malts that complement a hearty fall meal, this spiced up Imperial Porter will have you asking for a second helping.

This special beer is brewed for the best season of the year. It’s color resembles the falling leaves and the aroma and flavor will transport your senses to autumn. Brewed with a variety of spices and dry-spiced for additional character. It is like pumpkin pie in a glass without the crust and whipped cream.
With Ginger and nutmeg
Saison brewed with pumpkin and spices added just before kegging to produce a unique seasonal brew.
Dark, pretty color. Small hint of pumpkin but great overall taste.

This remarkable creation is the result of months of planning, patience and experimentation. We started with 50 lbs of pumpkin in our mash and added River Bend pilsner malt, which was smoked by 12 Bones Smokehouse. But we still weren’t satisfied. So we rolled out some rum barrels to age this special fall treat. Smoke forward in front, followed by a rum-sweet body, it finishes as dry and crisp as a fall afternoon.

Long Trail Imperial Pumpkin Ale is the first offering in Long Trail’s new Brush and Barrel Series. This limited release seasonal treat is small batch brewed with pumpkins, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, and cloves, with increased malts and a touch of bitterness for the perfect balance.

beer_name: Fermentation Without Representation Imperial Pumpkin Porter (release #15)
beer_description: On cask.
Medium bodied brown ale sweet dark malt flavor with a balancing bitterness. Spiced with traditional pumpkin pie spices and vanilla instead of finishing hops.
Fall seasonal, robust porter brewed with real pumpkin and spices.

Our handcrafted American harvest Pumpkin Ale, is the perfect synergy of unique brewing ingredients. Real pumpkin adds a full body and sweetness to this, reddish-amber brew.

Munich, caramel and 2-row pale malts deliver a distinct malty character that, when combined with traditional pumpkin pie spices, create the perfect union of both.
An homage to the now defunct Olde Towne Brewery classic.
Pumpkin ale aged on ginger
Blend between a stout and a porter...dark pumpkin!
All spice and fresh pumpkins

Brewed using real pumpkins and savory pumpkin pie spices giving hints of natural cinnamon and nutmeg. American hops balanced with Pale, Aromatic & Caramel malts create a full-bodied
taste and exceptional flavor.

beer_name: T.R.E.A.T. Imperial Chocolate Pumpkin Porter (Oak Aged)
beer_description: Oak Aged version of Midnight Suns Imperial Chocolate Pumpkin Porter. This oak-aged version won GOLD at GABF 2007.

beer_name: Off The Vine Imperial Pumpkin Ale
beer_description: Not your typical pumpkin beer, this seasonal ale is brewed with real roasted pumpkin, molasses, vanilla and classic pumpkin pie spices -- Grandma would approve! This beer has the flavor of the whole pie, from the crust all the way up to the dollop of Dream Whip on top. You've gotta taste it to believe it. Mmmmmmm...
A chocolate stout with a heavy dose of pumpkin and spice and a hint of vanilla.
This is a fun twist on a traditional Harvest Ale. We used nearly 100 lbs. of “Sweet Mama” pumpkins, brown sugar and a special blend of spices to create a mildly sweet brew for autumn.
Emerald City Stout with pumpkin.
Malty pumpkin beer brewed with 3 pounds of pumpkin PER KEG and a blend of local spices- cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, allspice and cloves. Same recipe is Cyclone Gloria (retired).

Pleasant as fall in the Ozarks! We use real pumpkin, premium barley, wheat, and flaked oats to provide a rich malty base with an exceptionally smooth body. A blend of 6 spices add that familiar taste you love about pumpkin pie. This brew is perfect for a crisp fall evening. Cheers!

beer_name: Pumpkin & Chai Spiced Ghost Pigeon Porter
beer_description: 200 lbs of roasted Coward Farms CT sugar pumpkins meld with the dark wheat for a very smooth taste and finish. Lightly spiced with nutmeg, cinnamon, and ginger.
A light brown ale that boasts sweet caramel malt flavor and hints of cocoa. The flavors are balanced with UW ACRES grown Pam Pumpkins and mild pumpkin pie spices.
Dark colored ale that is brewed with caramelized pumpkin, ginger, all spice, nutmeg and cinnamon. This is a dark colored beer that doesn't drink like one.
Some barrel funk in this.  I like
An earthy quality with subtle pumpkin & spice notes. Brewed with local pumpkins.
A fall seasonal ale brewed with cinnamon, all spice, nutmeg, ginger and clove.  Pumpkin mash is used throughout the process in the mash, the boil and the fermenter.
